976
00:57:47,719 --> 00:57:48,239
Rest assured.

977
00:57:49,119 --> 00:57:50,519
She won't be a problem for you.

978
00:57:50,719 --> 00:57:51,199
Why?

979
00:57:52,159 --> 00:57:53,159
Because you're talented.

980
00:57:58,440 --> 00:58:00,199
My Lady, where's Mr. Fan?

981
00:58:01,719 --> 00:58:02,360
He's over there.

982
00:58:04,920 --> 00:58:06,280
Now I understand why

983
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:07,199
she's called Imperial Consort Shu.
('Shu' is a homophone for 'book' in Chinese)

984
00:58:07,400 --> 00:58:07,880
What?

985
00:58:08,559 --> 00:58:09,039
Nothing.

986
00:58:10,039 --> 00:58:10,719
Mr. Fan,

987
00:58:10,920 --> 00:58:11,760
take a seat, please.

988
00:58:12,079 --> 00:58:13,840
Imperial Consort Shu will be here soon.

989
00:58:22,000 --> 00:58:23,199
Your Highness!

990
00:58:23,599 --> 00:58:24,760
Fan Xian is here.

991
00:58:33,800 --> 00:58:34,400
Take a seat.

992
00:58:47,000 --> 00:58:48,679
Put this book on the second layer of

993
00:58:48,679 --> 00:58:51,159
the second bookshelf on the left.

994
00:59:00,719 --> 00:59:02,079
Your poem is good.

995
00:59:03,400 --> 00:59:06,079
A thousand miles from home,
I'm grieved at autumn's plight;

996
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:08,960
Your Highness, I'm so flattered.

997
00:59:09,119 --> 00:59:10,159
Have you opened a bookstore?

998
00:59:10,480 --> 00:59:10,880
Yes.

999
00:59:11,239 --> 00:59:12,199
Do you have any unique copies?

1000
00:59:12,480 --> 00:59:14,079
We only have novels.

1001
00:59:14,079 --> 00:59:15,079
No ancient books actually.

1002
00:59:15,280 --> 00:59:18,199
I heard that you wrote the Red Mansions.

1003
00:59:19,079 --> 00:59:20,199
Actually it was written

1004
00:59:20,360 --> 00:59:21,440
by Mr. Cao.

1005
00:59:21,960 --> 00:59:23,119
I read it by chance,

1006
00:59:23,239 --> 00:59:23,960
and copied it.

1007
00:59:24,039 --> 00:59:25,199
Who is he?

1008
00:59:26,519 --> 00:59:28,400
I've been collecting essays
of ancient times.

1009
00:59:29,280 --> 00:59:30,480
How come I never heard of him?

1010
00:59:33,239 --> 00:59:34,920
Anyway, the book is really good.

1011
00:59:36,079 --> 00:59:37,519
Your Highness, I'm so flattered.

1012
00:59:39,960 --> 00:59:42,519
What have you been reading recently?

1013
00:59:43,679 --> 00:59:45,079
You publish the book. I will
take care of the network of shops.

1014
00:59:45,280 --> 00:59:45,880
And then we split the profit 40/60.

1015
00:59:46,119 --> 00:59:47,559
You get 60 and I get 40.
What do you think?

1016
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:48,960
The account books.

1017
00:59:49,280 --> 00:59:50,559
Business.

1018
00:59:52,719 --> 00:59:54,639
It's vulgar after all.

1019
00:59:55,519 --> 00:59:57,440
Your Highness, you're absolutely right.

1020
00:59:59,679 --> 01:00:01,320
Wan'er grew up in the imperial palace.

1021
01:00:01,960 --> 01:00:03,320
We all treat her as our daughter.

1022
01:00:03,960 --> 01:00:05,400
So I have to see you.

1023
01:00:06,599 --> 01:00:08,199
Chengze also speaks highly of you.

1024
01:00:08,920 --> 01:00:10,239
Who's Chengze?

1025
01:00:15,159 --> 01:00:16,320
Oh, it's the Second Prince.

1026
